                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On August 19 the State and Treasury Departments in a joint statement announced
                    that Secretary Snyder would preside as Chairman of meetings beginning September
                    6, which would carry forward the talks which Snyder had held with Cripps and
                    Abbott in London during July. For the full text of this statement, see
                    Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, August 29, 1949, page
                    307.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
